A manhunt is underway to find the suspects accused of killing an unidentified man following the gruesome discovery of a body of a man, believed to be in his late 20s, with multiple gunshot wounds in the Mhlasini area in Verulam, on Sunday. The discovery of the victim was made by a municipal worker who contacted the Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) headquarters requesting assistance for the man found laying unresponsive on Hazelmare Drive. RUSA spokesperson, Prem Balram, said officers and paramedics were dispatched to the location and on arrival found the man on the side of the road. “Paramedics assessed the patient who showed no signs of life and he was declared deceased on-scene.” Balram said the victim had suffered 10 gunshot wounds and three projectiles were also recovered on-scene. “The motive of the killing has not been established.” Communications officer for the South African Police Service in Verulam, Captain Henry Kisten said a murder docket was opened at the station and is currently under investigation.